  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">restore hope to 100 teenage mothers in cameroon.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">New Era Foundation in Bamenda Cameroon plans to train 100 teenage mothers who have lost hope in life as a result of unprepared motherhood and who are finding it difficult to cope with life to learn a trade which will enable them to become financially independent and learn about reproductive health.They will receive business training, vocational training, reproductive health education and will be given small interest free loans that will be repaid after a period of one year.</narrative>
  </description>
